1. Install the required tools:
- Install Java Development Kit (JDK) 8 or newer from the official Oracle website.
- Download the Minecraft Forge MDK (Mod Development Kit) for the Minecraft version you want to create the mod for: https://files.minecraftforge.net/
2. Setup Forge:
- Extract the downloaded MDK to a folder where you want to develop your mod.
- Open a terminal or command prompt in the extracted folder and run the following commands depending on your operating system:
- Windows: gradlew setupDecompWorkspace then gradlew eclipse
- MacOS/Linux: ./gradlew setupDecompWorkspace then ./gradlew eclipse
3. Import the project into your favorite IDE (Eclipse, IntelliJ, etc.) and create your mod:
- Create a new package in src/main/java with a unique name (e.g., com.example.superjump).
- Inside the package, create a new class called SuperJumpMod, and add the following code:

```java
package com.example.superjump;

import net.minecraftforge.common.MinecraftForge;
import net.minecraftforge.fml.common.Mod;
import net.minecraftforge.fml.common.event.FMLInitializationEvent;

@Mod(modid = SuperJumpMod.MODID, version = SuperJumpMod.VERSION, acceptedMinecraftVersions = "[1.12.2]") // Update the version according to your Minecraft version
public class SuperJumpMod {
    public static final String MODID = "superjump";
    public static final String VERSION = "1.0";

    @Mod.EventHandler
    public void init(FMLInitializationEvent event) {
        MinecraftForge.EVENT_BUS.register(new SuperJumpEventHandler());
    }
}
```

- Create another class in the same package called SuperJumpEventHandler, and add the following code:

```java
package com.example.superjump;

import net.minecraft.entity.player.EntityPlayer;
import net.minecraftforge.event.entity.living.LivingEvent.LivingJumpEvent;
import net.minecraftforge.fml.common.eventhandler.SubscribeEvent;

public class SuperJumpEventHandler {
    @SubscribeEvent
    public void onLivingJumpEvent(LivingJumpEvent event) {
        if (event.getEntity() instanceof EntityPlayer) {
            EntityPlayer player = (EntityPlayer) event.getEntity();
            player.motionY *= 2.0; // Adjust this value to modify the jump height
        }
    }
}
```

4. Build your mod:
- In your terminal or command prompt, navigate to your project folder and run the following command:
- Windows: gradlew build
- MacOS/Linux: ./gradlew build
- The compiled mod JAR file will be located in build/libs.
5. Install the mod:
- Make sure you have Minecraft Forge installed for the version of Minecraft you are targeting.
- Copy the JAR file from build/libs to your Minecraft mods folder (usually located in %APPDATA%\.minecraft\mods on Windows or ~/Library/Application Support/minecraft/mods on macOS).

Now, when you run Minecraft with the Forge profile, your jump height should be altered according to the value you set in the SuperJumpEventHandler class. Note that this example is for Minecraft 1.12.2, and you may need to make adjustments for other versions.

